{{Distinguish|Shale oil|Tight oil}}
{{short description|Organic-rich fine-grained sedimentary rock containing kerogen}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}
&lt;!-- Although both spellings—&quot;oil shale&quot; and &quot;oil-shale&quot;—are in use, this article uses the more common spelling &quot;oil shale&quot; in noun forms, resorting to the use of the hyphen for compound adjectival use for clarity per [[Hyphen#Compound modifiers]] --&gt;
{{Infobox rock
|name=Oil shale
|alternative_name=
|type=Sedimentary
|type_link=Sedimentary rock
|image=Oilshale.jpg
|caption=Combustion of oil shale
|composition={{Hlist|[[Kerogen]]|[[Quartz]]|[[Feldspar]]|&lt;br /&gt;[[Clay]]|[[Carbonate]]|[[Pyrite]]}}
|composition_secondary={{Hlist|[[Uranium]]|[[Iron]]|[[Vanadium]]|&lt;br /&gt;[[Nickel]]|[[Molybdenum]]}}
